@Node COTD101 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Nick Hathaway"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #101@{ub}

Hi, folks,

did you like yesterday's card ? Good. I did, too. And because I did, I opted
to make a "Dream-Card" mini-series of say eight cards. Almost all of these
have been suggested to Decipher and so we might see them sooner or later.
Until then, have fun.


    @{b}NICK HATHAWAY (*)@{ub}

    Personnel, Federation, rare, Dream Card.

    Integrity 2
    Cunning 11
    Strength 13

    OFFICER, ENGINEER x2, SECURITY, Biology x3, Kills one crewmember (random
    selection) every turn unless Empathy present. Command Star (*)

@{i}"After the utter destruction of the U.S.S. Stardust which left him as the
sole survivor, Lt. Hathaway was always hanging on the edge of madness."@{ui}

(*) I've changed the name of this card. Originally, it was named after a
former friend of mine who almost managed to destroy our club in a fit of
jealousy. His name shall remain unpublished. In my suggestion to Decipher
I've made this an "Aquiel Uhnari" card.


This was less of a card than of a concept, namely to create really strong
crewmembers and balance them with some kind of "casting cost" or "upkeep".
An ENGINEER x2 + SECURITY combination is awesome enough, with the added
Biology x3, and the Cunning and Strength he becomes way too strong.
There are a handful of missions he can solve alone and more than just a few
for which he requires the assistance of just one other personnel. (@{"Vekor" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD37"}
might come in handy.) And this is indeed one of his uses. Drop him somewhere,
have him solve a mission and then he kills himself. Neat and clean. But of
course, there is the other idea of keeping him around for all the abilities
he has to give, in which case you need some Empathy around (even 1/2 Empathy
will suffice. What ? 1/2 Empathy ? Right. That's another Dream card. [@{"#107" link COTD107},
and the only one I've never suggested to Decipher])

But let's assume you don't have that card @{"#107" link COTD107}. So we need to take a quick
look around our empaths. The two @{"Trois" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD39"}, Tam Elbrun and @{"Devinioni Ral" link COTD142}. That's
all we have. Best choice would be Tam Elbrun here. Now is this worth the
effort ? I'd say yes it is. Tam Elbrun is not that great, but you get an
overpowered @{"Roga Danar" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD18"} in return. Not too bad.


Favorite combo(s):

- Nick Hathaway + Tam Elbrun + @{"Vekor" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD37"}. A mini-away team that is all but
  dilemma-proof (except for that *+%$& Firestorm!)


Rating : 8.5 (again, this is only an about rating. I've used the cards only
for very few games.)


