@Node COTD103 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Court-Martial"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #103@{ub}

Hi, folks,

here's another little nasty surprise:


    @{b}COURT-MARTIAL@{ub}

    Interrupt, common, Dream card.

Play on an away team that just lost a member. Unless Bureaucracy (*) present,
its player loses 10 points.

@{i}"With the often unjust court-martials, the Admirality frequently piles the
insult of punishment on top of the injury of losing a valued crewmember."@{ui}

(*) Bureaucracy is a skill I invented to enhance a few of my Admiral
characters. You can substitute Leadership.


Try this with a Klingon Battle deck. Each time you win a battle, just drain
10 points from your opponent, too. Also works nicely with some of the middle-
strength dilemmas. (It is not usable with the @{"Crystalline Entity" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD52"} and not
very sensible with @{"Barclay's P. Disease" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD29"}.)

Of course, this works a little differently whether it is worded with
Leadership or Bureaucracy. Whilst Leadership is a skill useful in itself,
Bureaucracy was very much designed to be a "shortcut" skill present as an
alternative to some really hefty mission requirements and as a skill useful
to avoid some otherwise nasty plots.

In the Bureaucracy variant this is a bigger threat, especially to speed deck
players. With only a few (albeit good) Bureaucracy-capable cards you will be
in a little trouble getting them out. (I have made up only three of them.)
Also, Bureaucracy is a strategy in itself, so even if these cards were
available you might hit a few players with this.

With Leadership, at least the Federation won't have too much trouble getting
around this one.

If you want to experiment with Bureaucracy, here's a Bonus Card:


    @{b}Admiral Connaught Rossa@{ub}

    Personnel, Federation, uncommon, Dream Card.

    Integrity 8, Cunning 7, Strength 3

    OFFICER, Diplomacy, Bureaucracy, Anthropology, Honor. Command Star (*).

(From "Suddenly Human")


Favorite combo(s):

-  @{"Desert World" link COTD102} + Court-Martial. Two Dream cards for a dream combo.


Rating : 7.5 (Bureaucracy) / 6.5 (Leadership)


