@Node COTD104 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Parallels"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #104@{ub}

Hi, folks,

some of the best cards are made by combining several cards into one (a little
weaker of course). So is this one:


    @{b}PARALLELS@{ub}

    Event, rare, Dream Card.

Exchange any 2 of your cards of the same type. These may be cards in play,
in your hand, draw deck or discard pile.

@{i}"Parallel universes that touch each other are only very slightly different.
Sometimes a rift might allow passage between them."@{ui}


This beauty can perform several functions.

The first and most obvious is to retroactively change a random selection
death or running off into an "owner's choice" one. P*ssed off that your
@{"Beverly" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD22"} ran off to the farthest planet ? Exchange her with @{"Mot the Barber" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD24"}
(thereby effectively changing the @{"Female Love Interest" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD74"} into a
@{"Male Love Interest" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD74"}). Angry at losing your @{"Enterprise" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD3"} to a Ship Seizure ?
Transform a Shuttlecraft into a new @{"Enterprise" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD3"}...

But if you only think of this card as a resurrection card, you're missing
lots of its potential. It can also be used as a minor @{"Betazoid Gift Box" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD9"}
(exchanging a not-so-needed crewmember in play for the one you need JUST
NOW!). Or, replace your @{"Static Warp Bubble" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD48"} made useless by your opponent
having lost all cards with, say, a @{"Red Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"} or a @{"Genetronic Replicator" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD46"}.

The third use is similar but sometimes crucial. It also works as a nice little
Teleport. Need two Diplomacy for a @{"Q-Net" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD86"} but have @{"Sarek" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD72"} stuck on the other
side ? Exchange him with whatever crewmember you consider expendable.

The drawback of this card: It essentially costs you a turn. (Not an interrupt)
And, it costs you a card slot. But nonetheless, having double chances of
getting your @{"Red Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"} early or getting a crucial crewmember at the right
time are not chances to be neglected.


Favorite combo(s):

- As a rommie, move somewhere fast with a @{"Pi" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD60"}, then suddenly Parallel in
  your Warbird and FIRE!


Rating : 9.0


