@Node COTD106 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Beaming Clone"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #106@{ub}

Hi, folks,

want versatility taken to the extreme ? Use this personnel card:


    @{b}BEAMING CLONE@{ub}

    Personnel, Non-aligned, rare, Dream Card.

    Integrity *
    Cunning *
    Strength *

    Gets all skills and stats of one personnel of your choice at this
    outpost.

@{i}"Transporter Duplicates are the result of failed beaming under adverse cir-
cumstances. They share not only their DNA but also their memories with the
original."@{ui}

Picture: Two identical Starfleet Officers facing each other.


This is not a card for the beginner as it requires a good amount of planning
to use. First what you can NOT do with it: You cannot use it to get the @{"Data" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD7"}
or @{"Picard" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD1"} you urgently need when he's still buried in the draw deck. You can
only duplicate a personnel card already in play.

Situation one:
You want to form two crews, each with a @{"Roga Danar" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD18"}. No
trouble - clone him.

Situation two:
You need two of a skill you have only once (Diplomacy?). Clone the one person
with the skill.

Situation three:
You are playing a treaty deck. Your Rommie crew needs some Federation
support but you don't get the treaty card. Clone your Feddie and transfer
him to the Romulan ship (he's still non-aligned!)

The trouble with this: Timing! Once played, this clone can never again change
the person he mimicks. So play it too early and get stuck with a bad choice.
(However, there is a way out. Find a way to kill the clone and @{"Res-Q" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD28"} it.)


Favorite combo(s):

- Beaming clone + @{"Res-Q" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD28"}: Nice shapechanger


Rating : 10.0


