@Node COTD109 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Dr. Leah Brahms"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #109@{ub}

Hi, folks,

How about a little hologram ?


    @{b}DR. LEAH BRAHMS@{ub}

    Personnel, Federation, rare, Hologram, universal.

    Integrity 7
    Cunning 9
    Strength 2

    ENGINEER x2.

@{i}"Re-creation who said 'I'm with you every day, @{"Geordi" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD32"}. Every time you look at
this engine, you're looking at me. Every time you touch it, it's me.'"@{ui}


Whoa. Best Flavor Text in the game. Really. Apart from that - well, better
don't go too deeply into details.

Holograms have one of two uses:

a) Redshirting.
Not too bad an idea. But I'd
rather have some holo which is a little more useful in general play. Unless
I am desperate for @{"Nutational shields" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD40"}, I normally have enough ENGINEERS. And
if I look beyond ENGINEERing, there are better cards (one of which will be
discussed tomorrow:-) ).

b) Space missions.
Good, where are her SKILLS ???
