        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #150@{ub}

Hi, folks,

again a jubilee number and I'm almost out of ideas for what to do
as a soemwhat special issue, so I'll take up on an idea that
recently floated around the 'net and make it into a card, namely
a way to link card games:


    @{b}FANTASY WORLD@{ub}

    Dilemma, Planet, rare AU, Dream Card.

You and your opponent each pick up a MAGIC: THE GATHERING deck
and play a game, starting at 30 life. Winner of that game scores
his remaining life as points. If you do not know how to play
MAGIC, opponent gains 3 points. Discard Dilemma.

@{i}"@{"Q" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD30"} and several others lured the @{"Enterprise" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD3"} crew to worlds of
magical fantasy, having them play games for the entertainment
of the bored immortal."@{ui}


But this would be too cheap, just starting a subgame. So where's
the linking element ? Here:


    @{b}WORLD RIFT@{ub}

    Artifact, uncommon MAGIC (but distributed with STCCG/AU!), Dream Card.

    Casting Cost 0.

X, Tap: Put any Personnel you have in a running ST:CCG game
directly into play. Use it as a creature with Toughness =
INTEGRITY and Power = STRENGTH. X is the higher of the two
numbers. If the Personnel is killed, remove it from the ST:CCG
game, otherwise return it at end of subgame.

It has First Strike ability if CUNNING is 6 or higher.

@{i}"There's more where THAT came from"@{ui}



Cool ? Sure.

Get some strong but expendable guys into your STCCG crew, then
uncover the Fantasy World and produce a fast green deck with
several World Rifts. Summon the big hitters as fast as you can.

Try Taurik (8/7), Chris Hobson (6/6), Korris (8/8), L'Kor (7/7),
Tokath (6/6) or Movar (7/5) all of which don't have the greatest
STCCG skills but are very cost-effective strikers for the subgame
and you can even afford to get them terrored...

Fast 30 points, go to next location, lather, rinse, repeat.

I'd appreciate comments or (if you actually try them out) your
play experiences...

You can also try other card games:

@{b}MORIARTY'S SCHEMES@{ub}: Play INWO, winner gains 25 pts.
@{i}"Professor Moriarty plotted against the @{"Enterprise" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD3"} crew when he
found out he was trapped on the holodeck."@{ui}

and

@{b}TIME TRAVELERS@{ub}: INWO Group card, Pwr 1, Res 1, SCIENCE, SPACE, WEIRD.
Can use his action to bring one STCCG personnel from the main
game to your hand, who is treated as a Straight Government
Science Personality with Pwr = STR and Res = INT and one
outgoing control arrow at any position you choose.

Galactic Empires (use those ships!)

SW:CCG (obvious choice, isn't it ?)

