        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #153@{ub}

Hi, folks,

popular demand puts so much pressure on me to do a certain Fed
ship that I'll do the next best thing to keep you guys satisfied
until I get my copy of the real thing...

    @{b}U.S.S. ENTERPRISE-C@{ub}

    Ship, Federation, rare AU.

    Range 8
    Weapons 7
    Shields 8

    Requires 1 Command (*), 1 Staff (+), 1 AU icon.

    Enters play damaged at any location. Tractor Beam. AU icon.

@{i}"Predecessor of @{"U.S.S. Enterprise-D" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD3"}. Famous for heroic action in
Battle of Narendra III, where it also entered a temporal rift.
Commanded by @{"Rachel Garrett" link COTD160}."@{ui}


Okay, what do we have here ? Almost a U.S.S. Galaxy with one less
Range, but instead special ability that is not to be neglected.
Enters play at any location, damaged. Well, many people think
of this as just a way to recover a stranded crew. Not too bad,
though this will not happen to you too often. Here's a better
idea:

You know the Transwarp Conduit ? Here you get a Transwarp conduit
that is a little weaker (just adds 5 range instead of the full
amount), but stays around forever and can attack if commanded
by some non-aligned leader.

And there's another thing to it: It is affected by @{"Red Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"}, so it
can be played at no card cost, but it cannot be countered by @{"Amanda Rogers" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD31"}.
(Add an @{"Exocomp" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD56"} to make this card even more valuable!)

So you need that extra range ? You know what card to play.
Need something to remove that @{"Garbage Scow" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD84"} quickly without
killing the points ? Use the Enterprise-C and then use a
Near-Warp Transport to get your crew back if you need it this turn.

So the bottom line again is SPEED. Lotsa speed! And if you need
one less turn than your opponent to gain those 100 points you
know who wins the game...


