        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #158@{ub}

Hi, folks,

now that a certain Romulan fan has (very politely) apologized I'll show
I do not hold a grudge for long and proceed with something really
Romulan:


    @{b}DECIUS@{ub}

    Ship, Romulan, rare AU.

    Range 10
    Weapons 9
    Shields 8

    Requires 1 Command (*), 1 Staff (+), 1 AU.

    Cloaking Device, Holodeck, Tractor Beam, AU Icon.

@{i}"Powerful ship created in Barash's illusion. Commanded by Tomalak.
Transported Admiral @{"Picard" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD1"} and @{"Deanna Troi" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD39"} to a Romulan peace conference."@{ui}


Okay, for the Rommie fans, I'll take their "future" ship first, you'll
probably see the Future Enterprise and the @{"Fek'lhr" link COTD176} later on this
channel:-)

Anyway, the basic principle behind these three ships is simple: You get
an awesome ship but you dearly pay for it in terms of crew requirements.
Or in this particular case, do you really?

You need three personnel, as with any regular D'Deridex. The only
difference here is that instead of the second staff you need an AU
personnel. And this is, for our Romulan friends, NOT A GOOD THING (TM).

Actually, there's only two sensible solutions (@{"Cmdr Tomalak" link COTD167} sux and he
does not even gain the Captain's log benefit, @{"Ajur and Boratus" link COTD175} have
limited use and Mickey D. is just plain weak at the moment): Berlingoff
Rasmussen and (even though you don't make full use of his powers)
@{"Lakanta" link COTD145}. The latter will actually help you a lot as 10 range is FAST and
with a WNOHGB built in this is even faster!

