@Node COTD171 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Temporal Narcosis"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #171@{ub}

Hi, folks,

I've used so many smileys in COTD, today I'll let our good captain Jean-
Luc use one:


    @{b}TEMPORAL NARCOSIS@{ub}

    Interrupt, uncommon AU.

Plays when opponent uses @{"Horga'hn" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD10"}, @{"Revolving Door" link COTD168},
@{"Emergency Transporter Armbands" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD95"} or Energy Vortex.
Your next turn take a double turn. AU Icon.

@{i}"Debilitating disorientation caused by prolonged exposure to a temporal
disturbance, similar to nitrogen narcosis ('the bends'). @{"Jean-Luc Picard" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD1"}
experienced this in 2369."@{ui}


Hmm. Time Walk (for you Magic Guys)? Good thing to have. If it weren't
just for the fact that it has a prerequisite, so let's analyze that
first.

Your opponent must be using any one of:

@{"Horga'hn" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD10"}: Get your little revenge on him. When he takes double turns, you
are quite justified in doing the same, aren't you ? Too bad yours isn't
permanent but it might get you the one crucial turn.

@{"Revolving Door" link COTD168}: If he just use it to close your AU doorway, you have no
opportunity to play the Narcosis as you need an open door to be allowed
to throw it. So it only apples when your opponent uses the @{"revolving door" link CODT168}
to either reopen his AU door or to kill your @{"Iconian gateway" link COTD180}, both of
which will not be very common uses of the @{"Revolving door" link COTD168}.

@{"Emergency Transporter Armbands" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD95"}: Ah, so your opponent is playing the Oops
card? And then you need an extra turn to beat him? What do you think
the last 170 COTD's were for???

Energy Vortex: Hmm, finally a card we might see and still be able to use
our Temporal Narcosis. So we don't get to play our crucial card and get
an extra turn instead - after the opponent has another chance to do
whatever we wanted to stop him from with the card we just played.  But maybe
we get another turn - err two turns.

To summarize: We have an extra turn usable (a) for somewhat compensating
on an @{"Horga'hn" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD10"}, (b) when somebody closes your @{"Iconian Gateway" link COTD180} or opens
his AU door with a @{"revolving door" link COTD168} instead of a @{"Kevin" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD20"}, (c) when somebody
uses the Vortex to disturb us. (I don't count the @{"ETA" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD95"} here. You don't
need an extra turn if your opponent plays @{"ETA's" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD95"}. Trust me.)

In a tournament, of course you can just count on your opponent having a
@{"Horga'hn" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD10"}. Play your narcosis and get one turn - hopefully the one turn
you need to get your own @{"Horga'hn" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD10"}.

BTW: Timing here. It would be nice to nullify an attempt at closing your
AU door with a @{"Kevin" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD20"} and then to seek some revenge with an extra turn
from the narcosis. Too bad the @{i}"just played"@{ui} time frame ends as soon as
your @{"Kevin" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD20"} resolves :-(


