        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #172@{ub}

Hi, folks,

there are OFFICERs, ENGINEERs and CIVILIANs, but who can sport an ANIMAL?
Like a


    @{b}TARG@{ub}

    Personnel(?), Klingon, common AU.

    Integrity 4
    Cunning 1
    Strength 5

    ANIMAL, All non-Targ Klingons Strength +1 where present, Nullifies one
    just-played @{"Rogue Borg" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD33"} where present. Universal.

@{i}"Horned, furry, ferocious boar-like animal. A popular Klingon pet.
@{"Lieutenant Worf" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD35"} had one as a child. Heart of Targ is a Klingon delicacy.
This one is male."@{ui}


Whoops, as intelligent as @{"Fek'lhr" link COTD176} and that really means something for a
pig. The idea here is again having a combination of several cards put in
just one. You get a personnel card (well, something similar to a
personnel card), an equipment (half a Klingon disruptor) and a very
specialized reusable variant of @{"Amanda Rogers" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD31"}.

Actually, for evaluating the game effect, the first two functions can be
more or less combined into one, as ANIMAL is currently not a
classification with any use (this might change when Spot comes out) and
so the only value of a Targ besides being a possible Targ-et [pun
intended] for random selection deaths or random male runaways is the
attribute points it provides and its second function (the Strength
enhancer) is geared towards the same goal. So you might actually think of
it as a 4/1/11 card (in any decent away team), thus a slightly weaker
@{"Fek'lhr" link COTD176} you can use without a Holodeck or -projector.

The third function is actually quite interesting as it makes both
variants of the @{"Rogue Borg" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD33"} strategy somewhat more problematic. The "play
one, stop the away team" is ditched to half efficiency (as you will now
need two @{"RB" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD33"} for the same effect) and the "play a big lot and kill
everyone" variation suffers twice as both the added Strength and the
removed @{"RB" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD33"} will work very much in favor of the ship crew. And that's the
point why the Targ is not such a bad card to play. Many people would
probably have treasured an event that makes @{"Rogue Borg" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD33"} half as powerful
as before. Or an equipment that does this.

So why not make it a personnel card, cumulative, with the additional
benefit of some attribute points and the ability to make use of @{"Red Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"}
and @{"Lower Decks" link COTD188}? Hmm. Because nobody will want to play it, will they ?
Crazy world.


