@Node COTD173 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Senior Staff Meeting"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #173@{ub}

Hi, folks,

hope you are ready for the next shot of your favorite addiction:


    @{b}SENIOR STAFF MEETING@{ub}

    Interrupt, uncommon AU.

Plays on ship with OFFICER, ENGINEER, MEDICAL, SCIENCE and SECURITY
aboard, just before the initial attempt at a space mission. First Dilemma
encountered is discarded.

@{i}"Standard operating procedure on starships is to call a meeting of senior
officers or department heads to help find solutions to paramount
problems."@{ui}


Best flavor text in the game. And they want to make us believe they
didn't allude to certain contract troubles ? Yes, they have to say so
officially. But I am not so sure the last two words didn't just slip in
that card text by pure accident.

For the game, you can play three or four of these in a pure space mission
deck. You need five, sorry THREE personnel (Try @{"Wesley" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD26"}, @{"Roga Danar" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD18"} and
@{"Vekor" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD37"}!) to discard the first Dilemma at every space mission you attempt.

Your opponent cannot play more than 23 Dilemmas. At least ten of them are
probably planet only. Six more get effectively removed from the game by
you destroying the first Dilemma at every location. Whoops, seven left,
that makes it just one Dilemma at each mission instead of two (or four,
depends on your calculation).

[At least I hope this interpretation is correct. Because they never
clarified what first "encountered" means. Like the first turned up or the
first that is correctly seeded. Just a small difference when your
opponent has six unusable Dilemmas she can slip under the missions to
nullify your Meetings. But this would be against the game spirit as the
Incorrectly seeded Artifact / @{"Palor Toff" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD25"} combo that has already been
outlawed. So let's go by the second definition of "encountered".]

That's all ? Nope! There are those @{"Cryosatellite" link COTD169}/@{"Q" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD30"} players. You seed five
carefully selected Dilemmas designed to cripple your opponent, and she
just seeds a @{"Q" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD30"} below it and cruises through? Play the Staff meeting on
her ship and save your Q2 for that pesky @{"Kevin Uxbridge" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD20"}. Of course you'd
better scan the location first.

And yet another use: When your opponent has that *?'#$ @{"Receptacle Stones" link COTD163}
card on your key ship and you know exactly what nasties are going to
strike you soon, just nullify them before they can do more damage to you
than to her.

Moral: Never think a card has only one use. And don't think it's always
bad to play a card that nullifies some nasty for your opponent...


Favorite combo(s):

- 3 Senior Staff Meetings + 6 Space missions: How many Dilemmas ?


