        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #174@{ub}

Hi, folks,

you probably missed me already, but at the moment I have trouble putting
out any COTD's on the weekends as they all seem to get crammed with other
duties, so we will for the next few weeks be reduced to four or five
cards a week. Sorry for that.


    @{b}CAPTAIN'S LOG@{ub}

    Event, uncommon AU.

Plays on table. Any of your personnel aboard a ship he or she commanded
or captained (as referenced in ship lore) raises SHIELDS +3 and WEAPONS
+3. (Not cumulative)

@{i}"A commanding officer's journal of events. While on the surface of
El-Adrel IV, Tamarian @{"Captain Dathon" link COTD181} made entries into his log by hand."@{ui}


This is cute. An upgraded @{"Bynars Weapons Enhancement" link COTD197} and a kind of
@{"Nutational shields" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD40"}, combined in one card. And there are quite a few ships
this works on, and there are more that may get the benefit in future
expansions:

USS Phoenix             Cpt. Benjamin Maxwell
USS Sutherland          @{"Lt. Cmdr. Data" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD7"}
@{"USS Enterprise-C" link COTD153}        @{"Cpt. Rachel Garrett" link COTD160}
@{"IKC Pagh" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD70"}                Cpt. Kargan
IKC Hegh'ta             @{"Kurn" link COTD114}
Devoras                 @{"Adm. Mendak" link COTD113}
@{"Decius" link COTD158}                  Tomalak (NOT @{"Cmdr. Tomalak" link COTD167}!)
Gomtuu                  Tam Elbrun
@{"Mercenary Ship" link COTD137}          Baran
@{"Tama" link COTD164}                    @{"Dathon" link COTD181} [this is on the rules sheet]
*USS Yamato             (potential: Cpt. Varley)
*@{"USS Hood" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD82"}               (potential: Cpt. Robert DeSoto)

A few people have of course argued that the @{"Enterprise" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD3"} should also get
the benefit. I disagree here. The purpose behind this card was, amongst
others, to provide some extra play value to otherwise neglected cards and
definitely NOT to make @{"Picard" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD1"} and the @{"Enterprise" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD3"} even more desirable.

But I think there are two ships that SHOULD get the benefit, although by
strict rules interpretation, they are out of luck: The Khazara (@{"Toreth" link COTD189})
and the Haakona (potentially Taris). They both read "xxx's Warbird",
which by the rules is not a valid indication of Command. I disagree here,
as the spirit of the card is to add the bonus to any ship card that
mentions its commanding officer. [BTW: The rule sheet explains that
"@{"Dathon" link COTD181}, speaking first" is Tamarian for "He's the captain of the ship"
and thus valid.]

Good choices for the log? @{"Enterprise-C" link COTD153} (@{"Garrett" link COTD160} is a great card and if
you have attack authorization it might make a nice surprise attack),
Sutherland (7/10/10 for two crew is good and @{"Data" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD7"} is in most good Fed
decks anyway), @{"Decius" link COTD158} (10/12/11, best attack force for Romulans and the
only fast AU ship that gets the bonus), @{"Tama" link COTD164} (non-aligned and good, as is
@{"Dathon" link COTD181}) and the Hegh'ta (better than the @{"Pagh" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD70"} and 8/10/10 for one crew is
even better than the Sutherland! Also the @{"Pagh" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD70"} is a little dubious, too,
as it says "under the command of" and not "commanded by", but I am
nitpicking. Decipher should publish an official list here...)


And the last one is easily my

Favorite combo:

- Hegh'ta + @{"Kurn" link COTD114} + Captain's Log: Best addition to any Klingon attack
  fleet.


