@Node COTD179 "STCCG.guide/ST:CCG Card of the Day/Latinum Payoff"

        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #179@{ub}

Hi, folks,

here's something for a Klingon Armada deck:


    @{b}LATINUM PAYOFF@{ub}

    Interrupt, common AU.

Plays if Greed aboard your ship when it destroys another ship in battle.
X=3 bonus points for each OFFICER aboard destroyed ship. (Not cumulative)

@{i}"Gold-pressed latinum, which cannot be replicated, is a valuable metal
used as currency in many less-developed sectors, primarily outside
Federation space."@{ui}


This card makes an entirely new deck type possible: A deck that does
never even attempt to solve any missions! So don't care about putting
together good crews, just man your Armadas of K'Vort class ships with one
OFFICER each and blow away your opponent's ships! Try to seed a high
number of Dilemmas so you get to seed your outpost last and get it as
close as possible to your opponent's. Then, play five ships and five crew
(hopefully aided by @{"Red Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"} and some card-drawing ability). Wait until
she gets a ship out, then blow away the outpost. Then battle the ship and
play a Latinum payoff. 3 or 6 points - instant Victory and very hard to
defend against. There are unfortunately only three OFFICERs with Greed,
none of them universal, so you will need a little luck, but you can also
add the Duras family (all three leaders and greedy). Which means you need
only eleven cards to win (plus the one @{"Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"}). Seven of them in your
hand, five more to draw, that means five turns. Nearly no deck will get
any mission points that fast unless they have a very lucky draw.

BTW: You can get more than just the 3/officer out of one enemy ship. But
you need to destroy it with an Armada. The "not cumulative" means you
cannot play it twice on one ship, but if they attack together, they can
each gain the bonus. (Big unintended rules loophole!)

The card is thus interesting, however you will need to build an entire
deck around it. And that's its weakness. You cannot really just throw
it into a good deck in order to make it better. You have to build a new
one entirely from scratch. But try it - nasty surprise and even the best
defense will get your opponent only a draw.


Favorite combo(s):

- @{"B'Etor" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD55"} + Hegh'ta + Latinum Payoff + Opponent's Runabout!


