Hi, folks,

A card they obviously had to make. But then, couldn't it have done
something better ?


    @{b}THE MASK OF KORGANO@{ub}

    Event, common AU.

Plays on one of your personnel. While in play, changes it from normal to
AU icon personnel or vice versa.

@{i}"In legend, Masaka was chased by Korgano across the sky like the Terran
moon chases the sun. @{"Jean-Luc Picard" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD1"} masked himself as Korgano to fool
Masaka."@{ui}


Two uses, one card. So far this is good (remember my insistence on
flexibility ?) Use #1: Remove an AU icon from one of your personnel
cards. Oops. The only time I would prefer not having an AU icon is when I
have to play the card and my AU door somehow gets closed. But I cannot
use the mask on a personnel just being played (by card text and by the
rules - I cannot play an event in the same turn as personnel even with a
@{"Red Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"}). Net result: Nil.

Use #2: Add an AU icon. Better. I could need that to seed a personnel
under a @{"cryo" link COTD169}... NOT! It only works on cards in play, so again, zip.
Or, I could use the extra AU to add to the staffing requirements of a
good AU ship. Hmm. Shouldn't I rather put another AU personnel in my deck
instead? One that has an AU icon like the mask can give, but also adds
some skills and attributes and does not even cost me a turn when I have a
@{"Red Alert" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD6"}? Grmph.

But there is still one situation left open. What if I want to remove the
staffing requirements from one of my ships to stop it from moving ? Which
of course only applies when my ship is controlled by something nasty like
@{"Cytherians" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD47"}, as otherwise I can just stop. Hmm. @{"Cytherians" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD47"} or
@{"Incoming message" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD68"}? Why should I delay getting rid of the nasty if I cannot remove
it anyway ? And even if I would, why not just use an
@{"Emergency Transporter Armband" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD95"} and beam somebody off at the nearest planet ? Zero,
fourth time.

And that is the final rating for myself (you'll find some disagreement
from others) Zero. Err, One, to go by the rules.


Favorite combo(s):

- You playing a deck with 5 masks against me.


