        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #187@{ub}

Hi, folks,

I had some access trouble yesterday, so no COTD then, but I am back...
With the new top slot mission:


    @{b}DIPLOMATIC CONFERENCE@{ub}

    Mission, Planet,AU rare

    Span 4
    60 points
    Fed, Kli, Rom

One V.I.P from each of three affiliations + one non-aligned V.I.P.

@{i}"Parliament: Participate in historic interstellar conference at this
neutral diplomatic site."@{ui}


I have already seen several decks built around this card (with varying
success). It really is an "all or nothing" card. Not only do you need
four personnel from four different affiliations (thus requiring a 3-color
deck), but you also must overcome any Dilemmas seeded here, a task at
which the various V.I.P's will not excel.

Also, you will practically need to seed three outposts (possibly and best
all three at the Diplomatic Conference), as a neutral outpost would
require making three trips by ship to the conference location (can only
be seeded at space locations). And remember, your V.I.P.'s can only
cooperate here unless you have the appropriate treaty.

Personnel choices:

Non-aligned is quite easy. You will need all of them. All two. You cannot
afford having just one and your choice is not that good. I'd prefer
@{"Maques" link "STCCG:cotd300.guide/COTD218"} for the higher Integrity (Firestorms). Neither is AU (icon), so no
@{"Cryosatellite" link COTD169}, either.

Romulan: Your obvious choice should be @{"Major Rakal" link COTD147}. She is dual
affiliation, allowing you to use her as what you need, AU for your
@{"Cryosatellite" link COTD169} and she can ride your Fed ships even if you need her as a
Rommie later. For the second slot, I'd recommend @{"Sela" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD23"} or Pardek.

Klingon: They have more than enough V.I.P.'s, but the prime choice is
@{"Governor Worf" link COTD151} (AU and SECURITY), followed by the Duras clan and
@{"Gowron" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD5"}. Pick any complement for our fave ridge-guy.

Federation: Apart from the Janus-headed @{"Rakal" link COTD147}, @{"Sarek" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD72"} would probably be
your best choice (Mindmeld, nice to have against the "need ... x2"
Dilemmas). Beyond, you have to select between Tam Elbrun and Kareel Odan.
Again, no AU so no @{"Cryosatellite" link COTD169} (except @{"Rakal" link COTD147}, natch).

General result: The mission is too hard for 60 points. You still have to
solve a second mission and the skills needed don't really overlap
(although you might try First Contact and @{"Diplomacy mission" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD66} when mostly
Fed). Apart from the VIP's you at least need a @{"Vekor" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD37"} and a @{"Roga Danar" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD18"} for
the Dilemmas (two more cards) and a @{"Vulcan Mindmeld" link COTD132} in hand to flexibly
cope with some nasty Dilemmas. A theme deck card.


Favorite combo(s):

- Diplomatic Conference + @{"Sarek" link "STCCG:cotd100.guide/COTD72"} + @{"Rakal" link COTD147} + @{"Gov. Worf" link COTD151} +
  any non-aligned VIP.

- Diplomatic Conference + many (>=5) artifacts + @{"Ajur + Boratus" link COTD175} +
  Vorgon Raiders.

- (c) by Serge: Diplomatic Conference + @{"Devidian Door" link COTD146} +
  @{"Ophidian Cane" link COTD154}.
  Solves you some transportation troubles.


