        @{u}@{b}@{fg highlight}ST:CCG Card of the day@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

        @{b}Wesley's STCCG card of the day #200@{ub}

Hi, folks,

This is the day! And not a Captain's Holiday again (that one gets stale).
After scrambling through over 40 entries from 25 persons, I have finally
made some sense out of all the texts and picked the ten most interesting
cards (one from myself,nine from others). And to give the best chances to
everyone, I also restricted myself to one card for each person entering
something. So we have ten different authors for this nifty little ex-
pansion set. The question remained, where should I start. So I am going
in inverse ranking order, starting at 10th and going up to 1st. And the
ranking is not just mine but derived from the ratings I got in. And if
somebody gave a "coolness rating" besides the gameplay rating, I used the
former...

And here it comes...

Star Trek: Collectible Card Game
The Internet Expansion

Rank # 10, 557 points, Author: Isaac Garza.


    @{b}SPOT@{ub}

    Personnel, Federation, rare.

    Integrity 6
    Cunning 4
    Strength 1

    ANIMAL, All attributes +2 if Data present, attribute numbers can be
    switched around at will.

@{i}"Spot is Lt. Cmdr Data's pet cat. After experiencing several or her
appearance changes, Enterprise-D crewmembers have openly speculated that
she might indeed be a shapeshifter."@{ui}


That flavor text just did it. Besides a funny special ability, this
variant of Spot (I got four different of these kitties) actually reflects
best the one(s) that was/were on the show :-) Now for the game value of
the card. Before delving into strategy we have to clarify a timing
issue. You have a special ability that is played as an action (Swapping
stats). You can use it whenever an action is legal and this means not
during any other action (as it does not mention an action during whose
course it may be used). So you can use the ability whenever an interrupt
is legal, which does not include
- in the midst of an away team battle,
- during Dilemma resolution,
- between two Dilemmas if the crew or away team is unstopped,
- between the last Dilemma and the mission evaluation if the crew is
  unstopped.

So basically you have to decide on Spot's stats before any Mission
attempt or battle. But you can interrupt your opponent's announcing of a
battle to sharpen a few claws...

What can you gain? A 6/4/1 is nothing to write home about, and in the
skill department little Spot is less than well-equipped. Even using the
Data bonus you only have an 8/6/3 personnel whose special ability makes
it a somewhat weakened 8/8/8 without any skills. And that is not much in
a game whose nots and bolts are skills. But Spot might still come in
handy as an attribute provider when facing things like Hologram ruse (she
smelled something wrong), Shaka (cats' natural understanding),
Malfunctioning door (claws like steel) or battles (did you ever have 20
claws and 10 pounds of fur in your face?).

Better than a phaser or PADD anyway, as you can also boost integrity and
the bonus can be employed more variably.


Favorite combo(s):

- Spot + Data + Parallel Romance. Now THAT's a couple for a romantic
  evening! (Even better than the one somebody recently mailed me - the
  first time he used the Romance he hit Wes and Beverly.)


